BibtexBench() - Constructor for class bibtex.BibtexBench

Two abstract values concatenated by the hash-operator (#).
BibtexEntry - class bibtex.dom.BibtexEntry.
An entry is something that can be referenced by a latex file using the \cite command.
BibtexFile - class bibtex.dom.BibtexFile.
This is the root of a bibtex DOM tree and the factory for any bibtex model - the only way to create nodes.
BibtexFile() - Constructor for class bibtex.dom.BibtexFile
 
BibtexMacroDefinition - class bibtex.dom.BibtexMacroDefinition.
Bibtex let's you define macros which are essentially just shortcuts for strings.
BibtexMacroReference - class bibtex.dom.BibtexMacroReference.
A BibtexMacroReference references a BibtexMacroDefinition.
BibtexMultipleFieldValuesPolicy - class bibtex.parser.BibtexMultipleFieldValuesPolicy.
These constants determine how the parser deals with multiple values for the same field.
BibtexMultipleValues - class bibtex.dom.BibtexMultipleValues.
Some bibtex files have multiple values per field - this is a container that contains these values.
BibtexNode - class bibtex.dom.BibtexNode.
An abstract superclass for all bibtex model nodes.
BibtexParser - class bibtex.parser.BibtexParser.
The parser will parse the bibtex into a basic AST.
BibtexParser(boolean) - Constructor for class bibtex.parser.BibtexParser
 
BibtexPerson - class bibtex.dom.BibtexPerson.
BibtexPerson objects are elements of BibtexPersonLists, which can be used in author or editor fields.
BibtexPersonList - class bibtex.dom.BibtexPersonList.
A list of BibtexPerson objects that can be used for author or editor fields - use the PersonListExpander to convert all editor/author field values of a particular BibtexFile to BibtexPersonLists.
BibtexPreamble - class bibtex.dom.BibtexPreamble.
A preamble can be used to include pretty much arbitrary latex/tex at the beginning of a generated bibliography.
BibtexStandardMacros - class bibtex.dom.BibtexStandardMacros.
With standard macros we mean the ones defined in plain.bst
BibtexStandardMacros() - Constructor for class bibtex.dom.BibtexStandardMacros
 
BibtexString - class bibtex.dom.BibtexString.
A string - this class is used for numbers as well - if there's a number wrapped in here, the toString() method will be smart enough to leave out the braces, and thus print {1979} as 1979.
BibtexToplevelComment - class bibtex.dom.BibtexToplevelComment.
Toplevel comments wrap everything that is at the toplevel of a bibtex file and not parseable as some other entry.
bibtex - package bibtex
This package contains a driver for the parser that uses much of its functionality and is thus useful both as a demo of the parser and as a template for your own cut-and-paste programming ;-).
bibtex.dom - package bibtex.dom
This is an object model for parsed bibtex files.
bibtex.expansions - package bibtex.expansions
This package contains some add-ons that are useful for processing parsed bibtex further.
bibtex.parser - package bibtex.parser
The bibtex parser package - you'll have to pass a (possibly empty) bibtex model (a BibtexFile object) to the parse routine which will then populate it.

K

KEEP_ALL - Static variable in class bibtex.parser.BibtexMultipleFieldValuesPolicy
If a field in a bibtex entry has multiple values, then keep all of them.
KEEP_FIRST - Static variable in class bibtex.parser.BibtexMultipleFieldValuesPolicy
If a field in a bibtex entry has multiple values, then keep the first value and ignore the other values - this is what bibtex does, so it's the default.
KEEP_LAST - Static variable in class bibtex.parser.BibtexMultipleFieldValuesPolicy
If a field in a bibtex entry has multiple values, then keep the last value and ignore the other values.
